HEADWORD: Tee-to-tum
<hw>Tee-to"-tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Teetotaler</er>.]</ety> <def>A workingmen's resort conducted under
religious influences as a counteractant to the drinking saloon.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. or Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

